Tell about the space program?

The term "space program" in this context does not refer to outer space exploration. Instead, it refers to the planning and arrangement of spaces in buildings or other architectural projects. For example, in villas, the space program is designed to suit high-ranked employees and their families, with components reflecting privacy for both sexes and common interests for the family. In a hospital setting, the space program might include large lecture halls for professional continuing education programs.
What is esearch Building South

The South Research Building is a large structure whose exterior is made up of pre-cast concrete panels with an aluminum curtain wall and four-sided structural silicone adhered glazing. It serves as a gateway for entering the campus, with its main facade facing the boulevard to the south. The building consists of four stories plus a ground floor and a basement.

What is Exterior Sport and Play Surfaces

Exterior Sport and Play Surfaces refer to the outdoor areas designed for sports and recreational activities. These surfaces can be a combination of colored concrete or reconstituted rubber. They are designed to be durable for long-term use and maintenance.

Where is the parking level structure located?

The parking structure for visitors is located at the front side of the hospital, at the Wadi level underneath the main entrance level, connecting with the Mosque Plaza. It consists of two floors and one semi basement at the south. The staff's parking structures are located at the back side of the hospital.
